==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spindleworm
<hw>Spin"dle*worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The larva of a noctuid moth (<spn>Achatodes zeae</spn>) which feeds
inside the stalks of corn (maize), sometimes causing much damage. It is
smooth, with a black head and tail and a row of black dots across each
segment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spindling</ent>⟦br⟧
